Join John Olson (aka Inzane Johnny, of Wolf Eyes) and music writer Rich Tupica as they mine deep into Michigan's wilderness of sounds. No private press rarity is off limits: soul, gospel, oddities, punk, experimental, rockabilly, and garage rock. It's all unearthed. Strap in for an insanely bizarre ride across the Great Lakes State.

nts1.n: Fifth World w/ Ian Kim Judd & shiner: very special xmas mix 3 (R)
nts1.d: A riff on Jon Hassell's Fourth World series. Where Hassell focused on creating ritual music of potential societies that didn't exist; Ian Kim Judd seeks to evoke the notion of potential utopian societies that could exist. In these times of global instability and uncertainty, Fifth World seeks to posit an alternative, with scenes from an optimistic future.

Desire paths are formed by repeated deviation from official routes. Artist/producer Laura Groves explores private roads and dreamscapes with a series of mixtapes featuring demos, synth sketches, collaborations, pop classics, field recordings and soundtracks.
From the host: "An hour-long freeform piece. Home-recorded in one take, this piece builds on an earlier Desire Paths show which was itself fully improvised. I experiment with synthesiser and vocal layers; part of an ongoing sonic project exploring reclamation of memory and my upbringing in Bradford."

''In the Western world, improvisation is a failure; you do it when something goes wrong. But when black people improvise it's a form of mastery.'' 
Alba
Regular transmissions from the Japanese songwriter & composer Eiko Ishibashi, sharing favourites traversing folk, jazz, avant-garde composition and more.

nts2.d: From the host: back with some rare modal and post bop selections from the 3024 HQ in Washington DC, and celebrating the music and life of master drummer Jack DeJohnette who passed away this week.
integration sounds from the source; an invitation into the shadow.

In an time of almost surveillance-like coverage of popular musicians, where artists are expected to be 100% available and known to their fans, there stands Burial. Antithetical to the social media era, William Bevan continues to be (mostly) a figure of mystery to his legion of fans.  
His signature sound transmutes a postmodern patchwork of samples – R&B vocals, video game soundtracks, field-recorded ephemera, and organic percussive elements – into a club melancholia that could only come from London. 
Photo: Georgina Cooke

Berlin-based artist Pavel Milyakov aka Buttechno joins us for an hour a month.
From the Host: This episode includes music from Abigail Toll, Rian Treanor & Cara Tolmie, Ugnė Uma, Rat Heart, Chris Di Vito, Bill Orcutt, Mark Fell, lovesliescrushing, Maxime Denuc, Keiji Haino, Christoph De Babalon and a few of unreleased songs.

The premiere of Mark William Lewis' new mixtape, "Sparkles 22-24" - collating previously unheard recordings from March 2022 to December 2024, featuring alternating instrumentals and tracks with vocals. The mixtape is out 8th January via Bancamp.

Another utterly unpredictable guest hour from the singular Dutch selector DJ Marcelle ahead of a performance at Cafe Oto. 
Her new record Sorry No Silence is out now, with all proceeds going to The Palestine Children's Relief Fund.

Plunging into the mysterious and creatively-free world of Japanese record label DD Records. Founded by Kamada Tadashi in the early 1980s. The collective produced hundreds of cassette releases from their wider social and creative circle, like-minded in their disregard for genre restrictions and commerciality. 
Selected and mixed by NTS, featuring tracks from Phantom Limb's forthcoming reissue, Disk Musik: A DD. Records Compilation.

subtle.d: Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.
